items.name: Celeste Legacy
items.description:
Celeste is a general-purpose stable diffusion illustrations model. She seems to perform well with a smaller amount of prompts.

What sets Celeste apart from other AI art models is her ability to excel at both photorealistic and more abstract art-styles.

As it can be seen in the pictures below, she has been tested on a diverse variety of prompts, delivering quite good and fairly artistic results.

The example images have been generated using Celeste.ckpt at a low resolution and have been later upscaled using an upscaling algorithm since my GPU does not support any resolutions above 700x700.

items.name: ProtogEmb 2 (for SD 2.x 768)
items.description:
Same idea as the original ProtogEmb but retrained from scratch on SD 2.1 768 version.

Since the training images were higher quality it can output much more detailed pictures, I also expanded the base images for training from 67 to 92, all generated using Protogen 2.2/3.4 by Darkstorm2150

HOW TO USE

just drop it into your "embeddings" folder and type the name of the file in your prompt, you can also rename it to whatever you want and use that as the trigger.

Unlike most of SD 2.x you don't need a ton of negative prompts for it to look nice, I personally like to add "cartoon, 3d" to the negatives as the results end up looking higher fidelity.

HOW WAS IT MADE?

The images used to train it were from Protogen 2.2 and 3.4 using the base prompt darkstorm2150 used for the showcase images of the original models.

For this updated embedding I started by training a base in 1500 steps, then further bursts of 100 steps switching the datasets to focus and enhance any part I felt was lacking.

SPECS

8 vectors per token, 4000 steps, 92 base images (which were switched around for focused training), batch size of 4, prompt template being either style_filewords or a custom one which I edited according to what was the focus of the training, shuffle tags enabled, learning rate from 0.005 for general training to 0.0001 to focused training.

items.name: Deliberate
items.description:
Deliberate

All in One / Any Case Version

  1. The shorter the prompt – the better the result
    You can now forget about extremely detailed, 8k, hyperdetailed, masterpiece, etc. You can still use them, but it's not necessary, because you'll get a masterpiece anyway. Just take a look at the demo images and their EXIF data.
    Masterpiece tip:
    If you still gonna use masterpiece token in your Prompt, trust me, the real power of this token you can see only if you keep your Negative prompt empty.

  2. Trigger Words
    You can boost the result by adding the mj token (at the start of the prompt), cozy or cinematic. You probably guess what mj means and how the magic works. So you have it.

  3. Cinematic
    I've completely revamped the cinematic token. As you can see, Deliberate v3 always strives to find reflections and create stunning results (without crazy prompting), much like Midjourney does.
    At the same time, sometimes we want to achieve the highest level that no photographer can reach. That's why I've redefined the interpretation of cinematic.

  4. NSFW
    Oh yeah, I've rebuilt many of the NSFW tokens to deliver perfect results with just one word. You can find all the details on my Boosty page.

  5. Dataset
    The dataset is truly enormous. In fact, this is the first public model on the internet, where the selection of images was stricter than anywhere else, including Midjourney. Deliberate v3 can work without negatives and still produce masterpieces. This became possible precisely because of the huge dataset. It's unique, it's massive, and it includes only perfect images. Just try typing any word, exclude the negatives, and you'll see that Deliberate knows what to show you without randomness. Even when you're trying to get some ugly result, it still provides you with a spectacular one.

  6. License
    The license type is CC BY-NC-ND 4.0. If you want to use Deliberate on your service and/or for commercial purposes, message me on Discord. If you are an individual, not a commercial organization, there are no restrictions for you. The philosophy is very simple – private individuals provide support for the model, not companies, so private individuals can do anything.

  7. Easter Egg
    Now you can stop arguing with people to prove what the best sampler in the world is. You can prompt my nickname on a 512 x 512 and see how good the image looks, count how many fingers the girl has, and check if there is correct sign text or not.
    From now on, you can just run batch Euler a and UniPC, for example, and see who make the job better.

Have fun ❤

items.name: Pretty House So Excellent

However, this model may not be suitable for creating realistic people, as people typically appear in the background of photographs included in the dataset. That being said, when the phrase trigger word is not used or is de-emphasized by moving it to the end of the prompt, the effects can be quite interesting.

The examples I provide were made using the ckpt file.

I would love to see what you come up with so please post your results!

To trigger the style this model is is trained on use phse

items.name: CSGO Top View Map Layout Generator
items.description:
This is an AI model trained on CS:GO's radar top view images of many maps which can now produce custom map layouts in seconds. There are two different ways to generate layouts. One is with the tag "radar-topview" for a regular radar image like in CS:GO. Another way is with the tag "spectator-radar-topview", which produces a layout similar to the spectator radar in CS:GO. If you'd like to get a map layout similar to a specific map, you can add the map name before topview. So if I wanted a map generation which is similar to dust2, I would write "radar-dust2-topview"

Try the following prompt to get the best results:
"fps radar-topview game map, flat shading, soft shadows, global illumination"
"fps spectator-radar-topview game map, flat shading, soft shadows, global illumination"

Map Radar Topviews this AI was trained on:
de_dust2

de_inferno

de_nuke

de_mirage

de_cache

de_train

de_cobblestone

de_castle

de_overpass

Have fun generating map layouts!

items.name: WAS New Lara Croft (RotTR / SotTR)
items.description:
A textual inversion of 48 images from Rise of the Tomb Raider and Shadow of the Tomb Raider

Trigger Word: NewLaraCroft (Or whatever your filename is, apparently, for webui)

Notes:

  • Due to the dirt, wounds, and Lara's broad face in SotTR, it is necessary to state if she is "young" which tricks the base class of "woman" to be of fairer appearance. Otherwise she comes out like mid-late 40s in appearance.

  • Training data is from pre-rendered and in-game renders. Don't expect it to magically conform to photo realism models and prompts. You'll need some magic there, like modifiers, and/or blending the TI with an existing similar person: "((NewLaraCroft) mixed with ((Some Person)))"


Format is in .BIN, this is compatible with HuggingFace Diffusers and WebUI

items.name: Gold'n'glass
items.description:
The model was created for personal for editing anything photo, because I love all sorts of shiny realistic stones. The mindless generation of 100500 images of who knows who and why does not excite me at all, because I made the model exclusively for use in IMG2IMG, to simulate the material marble, porcelain interspersed with gold, but it turned out so good that I decided to share it.

I made this model last year, when there were no Textual Inversions, so this is 2GB and not 40kb. The recipe, how I did it, is unfortunately lost from the information of only 12 images used and 10,000 steps, that was a happy time of experimentation, because I can’t repeat this anymore.

Yes, and I barely found the recipe for creating Prompt, it's good that everything inside the pictures is saved.

Token to activate: goldenglass, although it is possible without it, there will be a picture without golden blotches, which usually spread over hair, mustaches, beards, eyebrows and eyelashes.

Prompt: [redshift style] goldenglass a marble statue, highly detailed, smooth, focus, black granite background, film, studio lighting

Negative prompt: cartoon, 3d, disfigured, bad art, deformed, poorly drawn, extra limbs, close up, b&w, weird colors, blurry:0.25

Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras, DPM++ SDE, DDIM, Euler a

CFG scale: 12-15

Size: 1920x1280, 768x1152, 768x960 (image resolution affects the final result no less than SEED, CFG or Denoise STR)

Steps: 25-40

Denoising strength: 0.25-0.38

Attention!!!

Denoising strength variations can both change the entire model, turning it into marble, and turning only a person into marble, without affecting clothing.

P.S. I would be very grateful if someone could point out similar models that are aimed specifically at IMG2IMG and do not change the recognition of the face, only changing the material or styling of the object.

items.name: concept-sheet
items.description:
This model is just the first dreambooth iteration for concept-sheet/old-books style. Based on SD 2.1

Installation:
As it is model based on 2.1 to make it work you need to use .yaml file with name of a model (vector-art.yaml). The yaml file is included here as well to download. Simply copy paste to the same folder as selected model file. Usually this is the models/Stable-diffusion one.

License and support:

If you like what I am doing and you want to support my current and upcoming projects: here is my coffee jar

You can use this model as you like. I love open source so have fun with it. :) If you like it I appreciate your support ^^
Cheers!

Black images issue:

2.1 models need to have a web-ui config modified - if you are getting black images - go to your config file and add to COMMANDLINE_ARGS= --no-half - potentially it could work with --xformers instead (if supported). This line might slow your generations a bit but will not affect negatively your output.



You will find example props on the images.

Embeddings:

This model works really well with various embeddings. I would recommend you especially these two:

  • https://civitai.com/models/4775/planit-a-documentation-embedding

  • https://civitai.com/models/4805/protogemb-2-for-sd-2x-768

items.name: RPG game character Portray creator
items.description:
This model is not about a hyperrealistic look. Instead, it aims to have imperfections in the picture with slightly off proportions to make it look somewhere between a sketch on the way to the actual painting without adding the small details. The model is trained on simplified digital pictures, and character portrays. It can be used for text-to-text or image-to-image to get the style and look of old-school RPG character pictures like you would find in the PC games of the 1990s and early 2000s or today in some of the independent game titles.

It’s also a good starting point if you need a picture as a basis to then draw yourself more details over it. Said something that can integrate into the creative process as an intermediate way of creating unique artwork.

items.name: Emotion-Puppeteer
items.description:
🎭 Emotion Puppeteer 🎭

UPDATE: Now available as a LoRA. Use with any model.

  • Photoreal faces with exact control of facial expressions

  • If you like the model, please post your generations!

  • Safetensors and inpaint models available on Huggingface, along with training details

  • These instruction apply to v2 only. There's no good reason to use v0.1.

Import Instructions

To get what you want, you should read this.

Use this prompt format for best results

  • "{A} face, {B} eyes, {C} mouth, {D}, {anything else}"

  • e.g. "plain face, seething eyes, screaming mouth, closeup portrait, looking away, old man with white hair"

  • CFG = 5 is recommended

A - Face keywords

  • plain, unattractive face - my subjective opinion - biased towards extreme emotions

  • cute, attractive face - my subjective opinion - biased towards pleasant emotions

  • adorable, most attractive face - my subjective opinion - strongly biased towards pleasant emotions

B - Eye keywords

  • seething, >: shaped brows - scrunched brows

  • grieving, <: shaped brows - scrunched brows

  • widening, eyelids raised very high - brows arched

  • glaring, lowered brows - eyelids lowered

  • pleasing, neutral brows - eyes crecent shaped and smile crinkled

  • piercing, neutral brows - eyelids neutral

  • squinting, lowered brows - eyelids squeezed closed or almost closed

  • winking, right eye open, left eye closes

C - Mouth keywords

  • breathing, mouth relaxed and slightly open

  • resting, neutral or slight relaxed frown - lips together

  • smiling, smiling with lips parted - teeth together or slightly apart

  • screaming, mouth wide open - lower-teeth visible or chin scrunched

  • sneering, nose scrunched - left upper-lip raised - upper-teeth not bared

  • singing, mouth wide open and oval-shaped

  • delighting, smiling with mouth wide open

  • kissing, puckered lips

  • gnashing, nose scrunched - upper-lip evenly raised - teeth together - lower-teeth bared

  • gasping, mouth open and frowning-bean-shaped - chin relaxed

  • relaxing, slight relaxed smile - lips together

  • frowning, chin and or nose scrunched - lips together

  • snarling, nose scrunched - upper-lip evenly raised - lower-teeth not bared

  • pouting, slight frown - lower-lip extended

  • grimacing, lips apart and stretched wide - lips apart - teeth may be visible

D - Other keywords

  • extreme closeup portrait, cropped at neck or closer

  • closeup portrait, cropped at shoulders

  • looking straight, head facing forward and eyes looking into the camera

  • lookway away, head turned to three-quarters, regardless of eye direction
